14 MODIFY REQUIREMENTS FOR COMPOSTING OF EQUINE AND BOVINE
15 MORTALITY
16 SECTION 9.(a) Definitions. – For purposes of this section, "Disposal Systems Rule"
17 means 15A NCAC 02T .0113 (Permitting By Regulation).
18 SECTION 9.(b) Disposal Systems Rule. – Until the effective date of the revised
19 permanent rules that the Environmental Management Commission is required to adopt pursuant
20 to subsection (d) of this section, the Commission shall implement the Disposal Systems Rule as
21 provided in subsection (c) of this section.
22 SECTION 9.(c) Implementation. – Notwithstanding any provision of Subchapter
23 02T of Title 15A of the North Carolina Administrative Code, and in addition to all disposal
24 systems permitted by regulation pursuant to subsection (a) of the Disposal Systems Rule on the
25 date this section becomes effective, the Environmental Management Commission shall also deem
26 a disposal system to be permitted pursuant to G.S. 143-215.1(b) and not require individual
27 permits or coverage under a general permit if the disposal system meets all of the following
28 criteria:
29 (1) The disposal system is used for equine or bovine composting.
30 (2) The disposal system does not result in any violations of surface water or
31 groundwater standards.
32 (3) The disposal system does not directly discharge to surface waters.
33 (4) The construction and operation of facilities, if any are included in the disposal
34 system, are approved by the North Carolina Department of Agriculture and
35 Consumer Services.
36 (5) The disposal system is approved by the State Veterinarian pursuant to
37 G.S. 106-403.
38 (6) In the event of an imminent threat of a contagious animal disease, any
39 emergency measure or procedure related to composting of animal mortality
40 pursuant to G.S. 106-399.4(a) is authorized.
41 SECTION 9.(d) Additional Rulemaking Authority. – The Commission shall adopt
42 a rule to amend the Disposal Systems Rule consistent with subsection (c) of this section.
43 Notwithstanding G.S. 150B-19(4), the amendment to the Disposal Systems Rule adopted by the
44 Commission pursuant to this section shall be substantively identical to the provisions of
45 subsection (c) of this section. Rules adopted pursuant to this section are not subject to Part 3 of
46 Article 2A of Chapter 150B of the General Statutes. Rules adopted pursuant to this section shall
47 become effective as provided in G.S. 150B-21.3(b1), as though 10 or more written objections
48 had been received as provided in G.S. 150B-21.3(b2).
49 SECTION 9.(e) Sunset. – This section expires when permanent rules adopted as
50 required by subsection (d) of this section become effective.
51
