21 (3) A complete copy of the labeling accompanying the pesticide and a statement
22 of all claims to be made for it including directions for use.
23 (4) If requested by the Board, a full description of the tests made and the results
24 thereof upon which the claims are based.
25 (5) In the case of renewal of registration, a statement with respect to information
26 which is different from that furnished when the pesticide was last registered.
27 (6) Repealed by Session Laws 2011-239, s. 1, effective June 23, 2011, and
28 applicable to applications for registration or renewals of registration filed on
29 or after that date.
30 (7) Any other information needed by the Board to determine the amount of annual
31 assessment payable by the applicant.
32 (b) The applicant shall pay an annual registration fee of one hundred fifty dollars
33 ($150.00) plus an additional annual assessment for each brand or grade of pesticide registered.
34 The annual assessment shall be fifty dollars ($50.00) if the applicant's gross sales of the pesticide
35 in this State for the preceding 12 months for the period ending September 30th were more than
36 five thousand dollars ($5,000.00) and twenty-five dollars ($25.00) if gross sales were less than
37 five thousand dollars ($5,000.00). set by the Board, not to exceed one hundred twenty-five dollars
38 ($125.00). An additional two hundred dollars ($200.00) delinquent registration penalty shall be
39 assessed against the registrant for each brand or grade of pesticide which is marketed in North
40 Carolina prior to registration as required by this Article. In the case of multi-year registration, the
41 annual fee and additional assessment for each year shall be paid at the time of the initial
42 registration. The Board shall give a pro rata refund of the registration fee and additional
43 assessment to the registrant in the event that registration is canceled by the Board or by the United
