6 DIRECT AGRICULTURE AND FORESTRY AWARENESS STUDY COMMISSION TO
7 STUDY LOW-HANGING COMMUNICATION LINES
8 SECTION 15. The Agriculture and Forestry Awareness Study Commission shall
9 collect information on communication lines that fall below the minimum height requirement and
10 create a public safety hazard, particularly to agricultural operations. In conducting the study, the
11 Commission shall seek input from the Office of Broadband Infrastructure of the Department of
12 Information Technology, telecommunications companies, agricultural trade associations,
13 commodity organizations, electric cooperatives, electric utility companies, third-party
14 contractors, and any other stakeholders the Commission deems necessary. The Commission shall
15 report its findings, including any recommendations or proposed legislation, prior to the
16 convening of the 2026 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
