18 REDUCE PENALTY FOR CERTAIN SHELLFISH AQUACULTURE VIOLATIONS
19 SECTION 16.(a) G.S. 113-187 reads as rewritten:
20 "§ 113-187. Penalties for violations of Subchapter and rules.
21 (a) Any person who participates in a commercial fishing operation conducted in violation
22 of any provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules or in an operation in connection
23 with which any vessel is used in violation of any provision of this Subchapter and its
24 implementing rules is guilty of a Class A1 misdemeanor.
25 (b) Any owner of a vessel who knowingly permits it to be used in violation of any
26 provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules is guilty of a Class A1 misdemeanor.
27 (c) Any person in charge of a commercial fishing operation conducted in violation of any
28 provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules or in charge of any vessel used in
29 violation of any provision of this Subchapter and its implementing rules is guilty of a Class A1
30 misdemeanor.
31 (d) Any person in charge of a commercial fishing operation conducted in violation of the
32 following provisions of this Subchapter or the following rules of the Marine Fisheries
33 Commission; and any person in charge of any vessel used in violation of the following provisions
34 of the Subchapter or the following rules, shall be guilty of a Class A1 misdemeanor. The
35 violations of the statute or the rules for which the penalty is mandatory are:
36 (1) Taking or attempting to take, possess, sell, or offer for sale any oysters,
37 mussels, or clams taken from areas closed by statute, rule, or proclamation
38 because of suspected pollution.
39 (2) Taking or attempting to take or have in possession aboard a vessel, shrimp
40 taken by the use of a trawl net, in areas not opened to shrimping, pulled by a
41 vessel not showing lights required by G.S. 75A-6 after sunset and before
42 sunrise.
43 (3) Using a trawl net in any coastal fishing waters closed by proclamation or rule
44 to trawl nets.
45 (4) Violating the provisions of a special permit or gear license issued by the
46 Department.
47 (5) Using or attempting to use any trawl net, long haul seine, swipe net,
48 mechanical methods for oyster or clam harvest or dredge in designated
49 primary nursery areas.
