General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (b) It is unlawful for any person without the authority of the owner of an aquaculture
2 facility to take fish or aquatic species being cultivated or reared by the owner from an aquaculture
3 facility.
4 (c) It is unlawful for any person to receive or possess fish or aquatic species stolen from
5 an aquaculture facility while knowing or having reasonable grounds to believe that the fish or
6 aquatic species are stolen.
7 (d) It is unlawful for any person to willfully destroy or injure an aquaculture facility or
8 aquatic species being reared in an aquaculture facility.
9 (e) Violation of subsections (b) or subsection (c) for fish or aquatic species valued at
10 more than four hundred dollars ($400.00) is punishable under G.S. 14-72. Violation of
11 subsections (b) or subsection (c) for fish or aquatic species valued at four hundred dollars
12 ($400.00) or less is a Class 1 misdemeanor.
13 (f) Violation of subsection subsections (b) or (d) is a Class 1 misdemeanor.punishable as
14 follows:
15 (1) For a first offense, the person is guilty of a Class H felony, punishable by a
16 fine of not less than two hundred fifty dollars ($250.00) in addition to any
17 other punishment prescribed for the offense.
18 (2) For a second or subsequent offense, the person is guilty of a Class G felony,
19 punishable by a fine of not less than five hundred dollars ($500.00) in addition
20 to any other punishment prescribed for the offense.
21 (g) In deciding to impose any sentence other than an active prison sentence, the
22 sentencing judge shall consider and may require, in accordance with G.S. 15A-1343, restitution
23 to the victim for the amount of damage to the aquaculture facility or aquatic species or for the
24 value of the stolen fish or aquatic species.
25 (h) The district attorney shall dismiss any case brought pursuant to subsections (b) and
26 (c) if defendant produces a notarized written authorization for taking fish or aquatic species from
27 the aquaculture facility or if the fish or aquatic species taken from a shellfish lease aquaculture
28 facility was not a shellfish authorized for cultivation on the lease."
29 SECTION 18.(d) This section becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to
30 offenses committed on or after that date.
