32 LIMIT LIABILITY FOR FIFRA-COMPLIANT LABELING
33 SECTION 19.(a) G.S. 99B-5 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
34 "(d) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, the duty of a manufacturer or seller of
35 a pesticide to warn a consumer or the public about the risks associated with the pesticide shall be
36 presumed to be satisfied if the pesticide bears the label approved by the United States
37 Environmental Protection Agency under the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act
38 (FIFRA) (7 U.S.C. § 136 et seq.) and the pesticide is registered with the Pesticide Board pursuant
39 to G.S. 143-442. This presumption may be rebutted only by a showing that the weight of the
40 scientific evidence does not support the scientific basis on which the required warning is
41 premised and that the manufacturer or seller knew or should have known at the time the pesticide
42 was sold that the required warning was not supported by the weight of scientific evidence. At a
43 minimum, evidence to rebut the presumption shall be academically peer reviewed, published in
44 a recognized academic journal, capable of replication, and reflected by a reliable application of
45 scientific principles and methods to the risks associated with the use of the product."
46 SECTION 19.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
47 actions filed on or after that date.
