49 ADD CERTAIN COMPOSTING FACILITIES TO THE DEFINITION OF
50 "AGRICULTURE"
51 SECTION 21. G.S. 106-581.1 reads as rewritten:
Senate Bill 639-Fifth Edition Page 13

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "§ 106-581.1. Agriculture defined.
2 For purposes of this Article, the terms "agriculture", "agricultural", and "farming" refer to all
3 of the following:
4 …
5 (8) The production, processing, storage, use, and sale of compost for agricultural,
6 residential, or commercial purposes by a permitted Small or Large Type 1,
7 Type 2, or Type 3 composting facility as defined in rules adopted by the
8 Environmental Management Commission. For the purposes of this section,
9 compost means a product made from organic plant, animal, or food waste and
10 created through controlled aerobic, biological decomposition of
11 biodegradable materials that, when subject to mesophilic and thermophilic
12 temperatures, stabilizes the carbon content, reduces the viability of pathogens
13 and vector attraction, and when added to soils is beneficial to plant growth."
