15 PROPANE ASSESSMENT AMENDMENTS
16 SECTION 21.1.(a) G.S. 119-63.4 reads as rewritten:
17 "§ 119-63.4. Referendum.
18 …
19 (c) The amount of the proposed assessment shall be stated on the referendum ballot. The
20 amount may not exceed the maximum allowable rate of two-tenths of one cent ($.002)
21 three-tenths of one cent ($.003) for each gallon of propane sold in this State by distributors to
22 dealers.
23 …
24 (f) A proposed assessment shall become effective if more than fifty percent (50%)
25 seventy-five percent (75%) of the eligible votes cast by dealers in the referendum are cast in favor
26 of the assessment and if more than fifty percent (50%) seventy-five percent (75%) of the eligible
27 votes cast by distributors in the referendum are cast in favor of the assessment. If the assessment
28 is approved by the referendum, then the Foundation shall notify the Department and the Alliance
29 of the amount of the assessment and the effective date of the assessment. The Department shall
30 notify all distributors and dealers of the assessment."
31 SECTION 21.1.(b) G.S. 119-63.6(a) reads as rewritten:
32 "(a) The Foundation shall use the funds to promote the common good, welfare, and
33 advancement of the propane industry, including, but not limited to, the following activities and
34 programs: education, training, safety compliance, equipment replacement for low-income
35 customers, marketing, advertising, promotion, workforce development, and customer rebates to
36 encourage energy-efficient appliance and equipment purchases by residential, commercial, or
37 agricultural consumers. The Foundation shall consult with the Alliance regarding its proposed
38 use of the funds. In addition, the Foundation shall consult with agricultural industry trade
39 associations and other organizations representing agricultural consumers of propane to ensure
40 that some programs and activities benefit the agriculture industry."
41 SECTION 21.1.(c) Subsection (a) of this section becomes effective January 1, 2026,
42 and applies to referenda conducted on or after that date. The remainder of this section is effective
43 when it becomes law.
