48 SECTION 21.2. G.S. 130A-343 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
49 "(j3) Authorize Certain Subsurface Dispersal Products for Use in Traffic-Rated Areas. – A
50 wastewater dispersal product approved pursuant to this section shall be approved for use in
51 stormwater and wastewater storage and dispersal under areas subject to vehicular traffic and
Page 14 Senate Bill 639-Fifth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 traffic-bearing loads if a professional engineer, licensed pursuant to Chapter 89C, certifies that
2 the product has been designed with a compatible load rating and the product manufacturer has
3 approved the product for use in traffic-rated areas. With respect to approvals already issued by
4 the Department or the Commission that include conditions or requirements regarding locating
5 qualifying subsurface dispersal products in traffic-rated areas, the Department or Commission,
6 as applicable, shall reissue those approvals, at the written request of the manufacturer, without
7 conditions or requirements regarding locating the product in traffic-rated areas. For the purposes
8 of this section, "traffic-rated areas" does not include Department of Transportation rated areas,
9 but does include driveways and private parking areas with impervious or pervious pavement
10 areas."
